s=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Value</span> → <span class=\"fn\">Pred</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">epost</span> : <span class=\"fn\">EPred</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A Hoare triple for reasoning about programs. A Hoare triple `Triple x pre post epost`\nis a *specification* for `x`: if assertion `pre` holds before `x`, then postcondition `post` holds\nafter running `x` (and `epost` handles any errors). ","docLink":"./Std/Internal/Do/Triple/Basic.html#Std.Internal.Do.Triple","kind":"structure","line":33,"name":"Std.Internal.Do.Triple","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Internal/Do/Triple/Basic.lean#L33-L40"}}],"imports":["Std.Internal.Do.ExceptPost","Std.Internal.Do.WP"],"instances":[],"name":"Std.Internal.Do.Triple.Basic"}